<h3>SCV sample SAS code </h3>
This directory contains a simple "Hello, World!" SAS code.
<br>
<h4>Interactive execution:</h4>
Start a <em>SAS</em> interactive session:<br>
<code>scc1% sas &</code><br>
In <em>SAS: Program Editor</em> window open <em>helloWorld.sas</em> program: <em>File -: Open</em>. To execute the program, select <em>Run</em> command in the menu. The output will be written into <em>Sas: Log</em> window. 
<br>

<h4>Interactive command line execution:</h4>
Start a <em>SAS</em> command line interactive session:<br>
<code>scc1% sas -nodms</code><br>
Type in the following commands at the SAS prompt:<br>
<code>&#62; put "Hello, World!";<br>
&#62; proc product_status; run;
</code><br>
To exit SAS, type in the following command (notice the dot at the end of the command!):<br>
<code>&#62; endsas;.</code>
<br>

<h4>Batch execution:</h4>
At the SCC prompt execute:<br>
<code>scc1% sas helloWorld.sas &</code><br>
The output will be written into <em>helloWorld.log</em> file.
<br>
<h4>Submit SAS job:</h4>
This directory contains a simple <em>SASjob</em> script that, when submitted to the batch system, will execute the <em>helloWorld.sas</em> script. To submit the job, type the following command at the SCC prompt:<br>
<code>% qsub SASjob</code><br>
Users who are members of any Medical Campus projects must also include their project group name:<br>
<code>% qsub -P <i>scv</i> SASjob</code><br>

<h4>Helpful Links:</h4>
